Police in Tzaneen in Limpopo have arrested a 59 year old man for raping a 15-year-old girl at Lorraine village in the Sekororo area last Wednesday. It is alleged that the suspect who is the former principal of a private school in Nkowa Nkowa outside Tzaneen called the girl out of the school premises saying that he wanted to give her a message.He subsequently took her to his home in Loraine village where on arrival he raped her.The victim opened a case and later the suspect handed himself over to the police.Henry Sephamu appeared briefly before the Lenyenye Magistrate s Court on Monday afternoon.He will appear again on Tuesday for a bail application Limpopo police spokesman Lt-Col Moatshe Ngoepe said.TimesLIVE